bradleyross.library.helpers

Class DirWalker.DirIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • bradleyross.library.helpers.DirWalker.DirIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<File>
    Enclosing class:
    DirWalker

    protected class DirWalker.DirIterator
extends Object
implements Iterator<File>
    This iterates through the directories.

    The current location in the tree is given by the structures levels and depth.

    Author:
    Bradley Ross

    • Field Detail

      • root

        protected File root

      • depth

        protected int depth
        Depth of the search tree.

        A value of zero means that there are no levels. A value of n means that there are n levels and the highest level is n-1.

      • levels

        protected ArrayList<DirWalker.Level> levels
        Array of Level objects representing the levels in the tree search.

        The current positions in the levels at the start of executing next represent the next item to be retrieved.
